{
  "texts": [
    "Even though the RNN output is based on previous calculations, long-term dependencies are still a challenging problem in RNN training [251].",
    "LSTM is a type of RNN that reduces this problem by preserving memory cells that act as summaries of the previous elements of the input sequence [252].",
    "LSTM is the development of the RNN hidden layer into a more detailed unit called a cell.",
    "Within the hidden layer, a cell consists of multiple gates that can be controlled to store or delete memory information along sequential input [157].",
    "Therefore, LSTM improves the ability to maintain remote context information."
  ]
}